The hole mobilities were studied by measuring the electrochemical impedance measurements on a symmetrical, hole-only device comprising of Au/HTM/Au architecture (Fig. 3a) under different voltage bias over 1 MHz to 100 Hz in the dark. A typical Nyquist plot of Au/WY-1/Au measured at −0.4 V bias was shown in Fig. 3b; data points were fitted using an equivalent circuit provided in the insert of Fig. 3b. The equivalent circuit contains a series resistance (R0), a charge transfer resistance (R1) and a constant phase element (CPE1) which associates with charge accumulation in the depletion layer near the interface of metal electrode (gold) and semiconductor (HTM)37, 38. Because the HTM is an organic semiconductor itself; therefore, R1 and CPE1 decreases when forward bias increases39. The hole mobility could be estimated using the equation (1):1μ=eL2kbTR1CPE1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
